    SuperIntArray
    more closely implements our in-class SuperIntArray, because it extends MyArrayList The one method that isn't the same after autoboxing is toArray(), because it returns an Integer[] instead of an int[], and due to Java's insufficient autoboxing, generic type erasure, and lack of true value types, it is impossible to write.
